qas.question: In what year were there two military coups in Nigeria?
Which group led the first 1966 coup?
Which Prime Minister was murdered in the Igbo coup?
Which Northern Premier was murdered in the Igbo coup?
Which Western Premier was murdered in the Igbo coup?

context: The disquilibrium and perceived corruption of the electoral and political process led, in <a0_0>1966<a0_0/>, to back-to-back military coups. The first coup was in January 1966 and was led by <a1_0>Igbo soldiers<a1_0/> under Majors Emmanuel Ifeajuna and Chukwuma Kaduna Nzeogwu. The coup plotters succeeded in murdering Prime Minister <a2_0>Abubakar Tafawa Balewa<a2_0/>, Premier <a3_0>Ahmadu Bello<a3_0/> of the Northern Region and Premier <a4_0>Ladoke Akintola<a4_0/> of the Western Region. But, the coup plotters struggled to form a central government. President Nwafor Orizu handed over government control to the Army, then under the command of another Igbo officer, General JTU Aguiyi-Ironsi.
